headline: Qualcomm forecasts first-quarter results above estimates as smartphone demand bounces back
summary: SAN FRANCISCO (Reuters) -Qualcomm on Wednesday forecast fiscal first-quarter sales and profit above ​Wall Street expectations, powered by a renewal of end-market demand in the smartphone industry.  For the current ‌fiscal first quarter, Qualcomm said it expects sales and adjusted profit with a midpoint of $12.2 billion and $3.40 per share,‌ above analyst estimates of $11.62 billion and $3.31 per share, according to LSEG data.  For the fiscal fourth quarter ended September 28, Qualcomm reported sales and adjusted profit of $11.27 billion and $3 per share, compared with Wall Street expectations of $10.79 billion and adjusted profit of $2.88 per share.
